\begin{verbatim}
ods(y, freq, pks_indices)
ods(Gyy, freq, pks_indices)
\end{verbatim}
Compute the operational deflection shapes (ODS) from response spectrum.

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{y::Matrix\{Complex\}}: Response spectrum matrix (n\emph{output x n}frequency)


\item \texttt{Gyy::Array\{Complex, 3\}}: Cross-spectral density matrix (n\emph{ouput x n}input x n\_frequency)


\item \texttt{freq}: Frequency vector (Hz)


\item \texttt{pks\_indices}: Indices of the peaks in the frequency vector


\item \texttt{min\_mac} (optional): Minimum MAC value to consider a candidate ODS for averaging

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{ods\_mode}: Operational deflection shape


\item \texttt{freq\_pks}: Frequencies at the peaks (Hz)

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Note}

\begin{itemize}
\item The ODS are normalized such that the maximum absolute value of each mode shape is 1.

\end{itemize}
